'''''Penicillium amagasakiense''''' is an [[anamorph]] [[fungus]] species of the genus of ''[[Penicillium]]''.<ref>[http://www.straininfo.net/strains/315874/browser ATCC]</ref><ref>[https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/63559 UniProt]</ref> The [[Glucose oxidase]] of ''Penicillium amagasakiense'' has been studied in detail because of the use of Glucose oxidase in [[biosensors]] and [[fermentation fluids]].<ref>[http://www.biochemj.org/bj/347/0553/3470553.pdf Conserved arginine-516 of Penicillium amagasakiense glucose oxidase isessential for the efficient binding of b-D-glucose]</ref>

